HEADWORD: Misprofess
<hw>Mis`pro*fess"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a
false profession; to make pretensions to skill which is not
possessed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misprofess</ent>⟦br⟧

